<Link id="l00120" /><CodeLine lineNumber="120"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// &quot;&lt;func name&gt;&quot;, &#123; &lt;leads&gt; &#125;, &#123; &lt;param rules&gt; &#125;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00121" /><CodeLine lineNumber="121"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// where:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00122" /><CodeLine lineNumber="122"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//  &lt;leads&gt; - list of integers that are one-based indexes of formal argument</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00123" /><CodeLine lineNumber="123"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    used to mangle a function name. Other argument types are derived from types</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00124" /><CodeLine lineNumber="124"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    of these &#39;leads&#39;. The order of integers in this list correspond to the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00125" /><CodeLine lineNumber="125"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    order in which these arguments are mangled in the EDG mangling scheme. The</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00126" /><CodeLine lineNumber="126"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    same order should be preserved for arguments in the AMDGPULibFunc structure</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00127" /><CodeLine lineNumber="127"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    when it is used for mangling. For example:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00128" /><CodeLine lineNumber="128"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    &#123; &quot;vstorea&#95;half&quot;, &#123;3,1&#125;, &#123;E&#95;ANY,EX&#95;SIZET,E&#95;ANY&#125;&#125;,</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00129" /><CodeLine lineNumber="129"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    will be mangled in EDG scheme as  vstorea&#95;half&#95;&lt;3dparam&gt;&#95;&lt;1stparam&gt;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00130" /><CodeLine lineNumber="130"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    When mangling from code use:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00131" /><CodeLine lineNumber="131"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    AMDGPULibFunc insc;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00132" /><CodeLine lineNumber="132"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    insc.param&#91;0&#93; = ... // describe 3rd parameter</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00133" /><CodeLine lineNumber="133"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    insc.param&#91;1&#93; = ... // describe 1rd parameter</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00134" /><CodeLine lineNumber="134"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00135" /><CodeLine lineNumber="135"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// &lt;param rules&gt; - list of rules used to derive all of the function formal</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00136" /><CodeLine lineNumber="136"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    argument types. EX&#95; prefixed are simple types, other derived from the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00137" /><CodeLine lineNumber="137"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    latest &#39;lead&#39; argument type in the order of encoding from first to last.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00138" /><CodeLine lineNumber="138"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    E&#95;ANY - use prev lead type, E&#95;CONSTPTR&#95;ANY - make const pointer out of</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00139" /><CodeLine lineNumber="139"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//    prev lead type, etc. see ParamIterator::getNextParam() for details.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00827" /><CodeLine lineNumber="827"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00828" /><CodeLine lineNumber="828"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Itanium mangling ABI 5.1.8. Compression:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00829" /><CodeLine lineNumber="829"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Logically, the substitutable components of a mangled name are considered</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00830" /><CodeLine lineNumber="830"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// left-to-right, components before the composite structure of which they</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00831" /><CodeLine lineNumber="831"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// are a part. If a component has been encountered before, it is substituted</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00832" /><CodeLine lineNumber="832"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// as described below. This decision is independent of whether its components</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00833" /><CodeLine lineNumber="833"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// have been substituted, so an implementation may optimize by considering</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
